title: RIM (BlackBerry) Wireless Device Command-Line Programmer Version
description:
Here is the RIM Wireless Device Command-Line Programmer Version 3.9.0.49 which you may know as cfp.exe, loader.exe or hahanew.exe. It is used for many things including re-enabling mass storage mode on your BlackBerry if it has gotten disabled. The other major use of it is to load either the factory OS (usually an MFI file) or the regular OS (usually an SFI file).

This program runs from the command line in Windows or can be called from a batch file if desired.
